OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1777449958
OL,3,CKing to speak of 'reconciliation' in
OL,4,Chistoric Congress speech
OL,6,FThe King and Queen were welcomed by
OL,7,Fthe US President and First Lady at the
OL,8,FWhite House on Monday, as GMB's
OL,9,FJonathan Swain reports from Washington
OL,10,FDC
OL,12,FThe King will offer "the highest
OL,13,Fregard and friendship of the British
OL,14,Fpeople" to the United States on
OL,15,FTuesday as he becomes the second
OL,16,Fmonarch in history to address a joint
OL,17,Fmeeting of Congress.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1777449958
OL,3,CKing to speak of 'reconciliation' in
OL,4,Chistoric Congress speech
OL,6,FWhile the UK and the US have not
OL,7,Falways agreed on everything, shared
OL,8,Ftraditions mean "time and time again,
OL,9,Four two countries have always found
OL,10,Fways to come together", the monarch is
OL,11,Fset to tell both houses of US Congress
OL,12,Fon the 250th anniversary of American
OL,13,Findependence.
OL,15,FIn a nod to recent tensions over the
OL,16,FUS war in Iran, King Charles will
OL,17,Freflect on the foundations of
OL,18,F"democratic, legal and social
OL,19,Ftraditions" and point out how the two
OL,20,Fnations have stood together throughout
OL,21,Fhistory.
OL,26,@pD@QOUrD@VO]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
